Script to easily block and unblock an IP address via iptables.
Author: Matt Gehrisch
Author Email: matt@gehrisch.us

To block an IP address (192.168.1.100):
ipblock -b 192.168.1.100

To unblock the IP address (192.168.1.100):
ipblock -u 192.168.1.100

Modifying iptables rules requires root privileges.  Use sudo (or root if you must).

Tested on: Ubuntu 12.04 and CentOS 6.4
